<title>USA: Movado sets 5-for-4 stock split.</title>
<headline>Movado sets 5-for-4 stock split.</headline>
<dateline>LYNDHURST, N.J. 1997-04-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Movado Group Inc said Monday its board had approved a five-for-four stock split, payable May 1. record April 21.</p>
<p>The company said it will maintain its current quarterly dividend of $0.03 a share. On a post-split basis, the dividend is being increased 25 percent, Movado said.</p>
<p>Movado makes Movado, Concord and ESQ watches and is exclusive distributor of Swiss-made Piaget and Corum watches in the U.S., Canada, Central America and the Caribbean.  </p>
<p>--</p>
